<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Support — Everest</title>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Sora:wght@500;600;700&family=Inter:wght@400;500;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  :root {
    --summit-navy: #1F4E6B;
    --summit-gold: #FFB026;
    --slate-azure: #4E7193;
    --summit-cream: #F0E7D5;
    --warm-white: #FFFDF8;
    --basecamp-ink: #1B242B;
  }
  * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
  body {
    background: var(--warm-white);
    color: var(--basecamp-ink);
    font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  }
  .wrap { max-width: 42rem; margin: 0 auto; padding: 3.5rem 1.5rem 5rem; }
  .wordmark {
    font-family: 'Sora', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--summit-navy);
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  h1 {
    font-family: 'Sora', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 5vw, 2.375rem);
    color: var(--summit-navy);
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-top: 2.25rem;
  }
  .lede { color: var(--slate-azure); margin-top: 0.75rem; font-size: 1.0625rem; }
  .ridge { margin: 2rem 0 2.5rem; display: block; width: 100%; height: auto; }
  h2 {
    font-family: 'Sora', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--summit-navy);
    margin: 2.5rem 0 0.75rem;
  }
  p { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  a { color: var(--slate-azure); text-underline-offset: 3px; }
  a:hover { color: var(--summit-navy); }
  a:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid var(--summit-navy); outline-offset: 3px; border-radius: 2px; }
  .contact-card {
    background: var(--summit-cream);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.375rem 1.5rem;
    margin: 0.25rem 0 1rem;
  }
  .contact-card p { margin: 0; }
  .contact-card .label {
    font-family: 'Sora', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--summit-navy);
    margin-bottom: 0.375rem;
  }
  .contact-card a {
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--summit-navy);
  }
  .faq-item { margin-bottom: 1.75rem; }
  .faq-item h3 {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    color: var(--summit-navy);
    margin-bottom: 0.375rem;
  }
  .faq-item p { margin-bottom: 0; }
  footer {
    margin-top: 4rem;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--summit-cream);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--slate-azure);
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="wrap">
  <header>
    <span class="wordmark">Everest</span>
  </header>

  <h1>Support</h1>
  <p class="lede">Everest helps you spend less time on your phone and more time in the real world. If something isn't working — or you just have a question — we're glad to help.</p>

  <h2>Get in touch</h2>
  <div class="contact-card">
    <p class="label">Email support</p>
    <p><a href="mailto:liberationwitheverest@gmail.com">liberationwitheverest@gmail.com</a></p>
  </div>
  <p>We aim to reply within 3 business days. Including your iOS version and a description of what you were doing when the problem occurred helps us fix things faster.</p>

  <h2>Common questions</h2>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>App blocking isn't working.</h3>
    <p>Blocking requires Screen Time permission. Check Settings &gt; Screen Time and make sure Everest is allowed. If a specific app slips through, try re-selecting it individually in Everest's app picker rather than choosing only a category — iOS applies individual selections more reliably.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>The focus timer stops counting.</h3>
    <p>The timer runs only while your phone is face-down — that's the point! Set your phone screen-side down on a flat surface and the timer will resume.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>How do I manage permissions?</h3>
    <p>Everest asks for Screen Time, location, and notification access only when a feature needs it. You can change any of these at any time in your iPhone's Settings app under Everest.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>Does Everest collect my data?</h3>
    <p>No. There are no accounts, and your screen time, location, and motion data never leave your device. The details are in our <a href="./privacy.html">privacy policy</a>.</p>
  </div>

  <footer>
    <p>Everest &nbsp;·&nbsp; <a href="./privacy.html">Privacy Policy</a></p>
  </footer>
</div>
</body>
</html>
